<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="float-v">float <strong><em>v</em></strong></h1>
<p>英 /fləʊt/    美 /floʊt/  </p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1-vt-vi-sink">1.★ <strong>vt &amp; vi (使) 漂浮 【反 sink】；(使) 漂流：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>The boy floated his toy boat in the shallow water.
那男孩把玩具船放在浅水中漂浮。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Wood floats on water. 
木头浮在水面上。</p></div>

<h4 id="2vt">2.<strong>vt提出；提请考虑（想法或计划）</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>We floated the idea to my mum of sharing a house.
我们向母亲提出了住在一起的想法。</p><footer>2020全国</footer></div>

<h2 id="_2">真题解析</h2>
<ol>
<li>If steel is heavier than water, why are ships able to <strong><em>_</em></strong> (漂浮) on the sea?  （2015 浙江改）  </li>
</ol>
<p>答案：
1. float  </p></div>